  "root_text": {
    "iti39:0.1": "Itivuttaka 39 ",
    "iti39:0.2": "Dukanipāta ",
    "iti39:0.3": "Dutiyavagga ",
    "iti39:0.4": "Desanāsutta ",
    "iti39:1.1": "Vuttañhetaṁ bhagavatā vuttamarahatāti me sutaṁ: ",
    "iti39:2.1": "“Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa dve dhammadesanā pariyāyena bhavanti. ",
    "iti39:2.2": "Katamā dve? ",
    "iti39:2.3": "‘Pāpaṁ pāpakato passathā’ti—",
    "iti39:2.4": "ayaṁ paṭhamā dhammadesanā; ",
    "iti39:2.5": "‘pāpaṁ pāpakato disvā tattha nibbindatha virajjatha vimuccathā’ti—",
    "iti39:2.6": "ayaṁ dutiyā dhammadesanā. ",
    "iti39:2.7": "Tathāgatassa, bhikkhave, arahato sammāsambuddhassa imā dve dhammadesanā pariyāyena bhavantī”ti. ",
    "iti39:2.8": "Etamatthaṁ bhagavā avoca. ",
    "iti39:2.9": "Tatthetaṁ iti vuccati: ",
    "iti39:3.1": "“Tathāgatassa buddhassa, ",
    "iti39:3.2": "sabbabhūtānukampino; ",
    "iti39:3.3": "Pariyāyavacanaṁ passa, ",
    "iti39:3.4": "dve ca dhammā pakāsitā. ",
    "iti39:4.1": "Pāpakaṁ passatha cetaṁ, ",
    "iti39:4.2": "tattha cāpi virajjatha; ",
    "iti39:4.3": "Tato virattacittāse, ",
    "iti39:4.4": "dukkhassantaṁ karissathā”ti. ",
    "iti39:5.1": "Ayampi attho vutto bhagavatā, iti me sutanti. ",
    "iti39:5.2": "Dutiyaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "iti39:0.1": "So It Was Said 39 ",
    "iti39:0.2": "The Book of the Twos ",
    "iti39:0.3": "Chapter Two ",
    "iti39:0.4": "Teaching ",
    "iti39:1.1": "This was said by the Buddha, the Perfected One: that is what I heard. ",
    "iti39:2.1": "“Mendicants, the Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha has two approaches to teaching Dhamma. ",
    "iti39:2.2": "What two? ",
    "iti39:2.3": "‘See evil as evil’—",
    "iti39:2.4": "this is the first approach to teaching Dhamma. ",
    "iti39:2.5": "‘Having seen evil as evil, be disillusioned, dispassionate, and freed from it’—",
    "iti39:2.6": "this is the second approach to teaching Dhamma. ",
    "iti39:2.7": "The Realized One, the perfected one, the fully awakened Buddha has these two approaches to teaching Dhamma.” ",
    "iti39:2.8": "The Buddha spoke this matter. ",
    "iti39:2.9": "On this it is said: ",
    "iti39:3.1": "“See the two approaches for ",
    "iti39:3.2": "explaining the Dhamma ",
    "iti39:3.3": "used by the Realized One, the Buddha, ",
    "iti39:3.4": "compassionate for all beings: ",
    "iti39:4.1": "see that that is evil, ",
    "iti39:4.2": "and be dispassionate towards it. ",
    "iti39:4.3": "Then, with a mind free of desire, ",
    "iti39:4.4": "you will make an end of suffering.” ",
    "iti39:5.1": "This too is a matter that was spoken by the Blessed One: that is what I heard. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "iti39:4.1": "cetaṁ → chekā (sya-all); cekaṁ (pts-vp-pli1) "
